result.execSummary:
Seth A Buckles was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Seth A Buckles was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 11:31 AM Defendant Seth A Buckles in court, in custody - appears in person.  Plaintiff Forest County District Attorney in court.  Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court confirms that the defendant sitting at defense table is Seth Buckles, confirms that the defendant wants to waive his right to an extradition hearing, does verbal colloquy as it relates to waiving hearing, defendant confirms that he is waiving extradition and signs the form in Court. Court goes over waiver form, defendant has read it and states it is true and correct and that is his signature on the form, executes that it was signed today in the Court's presence, defendant can be returned to the State of Kentucky.
